<p>Aaron: Dean is not &#8220;angry&#8221; and the press that tells you so is lying.</p>

<p>Fact: Dean lost Iowa because he shouted down an Iowa farmer during a campaign Q&amp;A session, saying &#8220;George Bush is not my neighbor&#8221; and going off on a three-minute rant. That had <em>nothing</em> to do with the scream. And of the reports that I read about the scream, I cannot recall any advancing the sense that Dean was <em>angry.</em> Rather, the frame I saw advanced was that he lost control. Big difference, there, Aaron.</p>

<p>By the way, I notice that you summarize what the media said, but fail to provide us with any links or excerpts. Could it be that you&#8217;re playing just as fast and loose with the facts as the media is?</p>

